- Patches -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This directory contains patches that add functionality into other services so that Nefarious IRCu will work with them
better. Patches can be submitted and requested on http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=533683&group_id=72192&func=browse
Please submit patches in unified format (-puN) and optionally include a diffstat output at the top of the patch. We 
will usually generate one if one doesnt exist. If you have any problems with any of the patches listed below then 
contact the Author (see the author table). If you get no joy out of them then contact us on irc.afternet.org #evilnet 
or the support tracker (http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=533682&group_id=72192&func=browse).

- Applying Patches ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

cd services.source.dir
patch -p0 < /path/to/nefarious/patches/patch.diff

Then remake your services according as to how they should be made.


Patch			Version For 		Description					Requires
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
banexempts.srvx2.diff	0.2	Afternet SRVX2	Adds in support so that SRVX2 will not die	Nefarious IRCu 0.3.0+
						when it recieves a burst containing ban
						exempts.
halfops.srvx2.diff	0.1	Afternet SRVX2	Adds in support so that SRVX2 can handle	Nefarious IRCu 0.3.0+
						halfops.
loc.srvx2.diff		0.1	Afternet SRVX2	Adds in support so that SRVX2 will properly	Nefarious IRCu 0.4.0+
						handle login on connect messages from
						Nefarious.


